This means you are trying to query the database directly for a CartOffline object without providing a [TypeConverter][1]. Room can only convert complex data to a [SQLite primitive type][2], i.e. TEXT if you provide a TypeConverter.

More info: [Referencing complex data using Room][3]

You have to create a class that contains methods that convert the type returned (or taken as parameter) by your DAO queries into SQLite primitive equivalents and vice-versa, so Room knows how to convert a Cursor to your DAO query&#39;s return/parameter type.

For example, your getCartProduct() query returns List&lt;CartOffline&gt;, so you probably want to parse that into a JSON String that will get stored as SQLite TEXT (you could also parse it differently and store it as BLOB). You can use JSON libraries like Moshi or GSON for that.

(Apologies if there are any typos in the code, but I switched to Kotlin some time ago and my Java is getting rusty.)

     public static class Converters {
       @TypeConverter
       public List&lt;CartOffline&gt; fromJSON(String json) {
    
         //here goes code to parse a JSON String into a List&lt;CartOffline&gt;
         //using your JSON library of choice
       
         return listOfCartOffline;
       }
    
