       public String fromListOfCartOffline(List&lt;CartOffline&gt; listOfCartOffline) {

         //here goes code to parse List&lt;CartOffline&gt; into a JSON string
         //using your JSON library of choice
       
         return json;
       }
      }

By annotating those methods with @TypeConverter, Room automatically knows how to convert your objects into SQLite types. You will need a converter pair for every non-primitive type that your DAO methods return or take as parameter. If your queries only return primitives like Strings, Integers, or  collections of them (like List&lt;Int&gt;), you should not need a @TypeConverter.


